Description for alphabet_warp: 
-- This folder was dedicated to seeing the creativity the Warp terminal can potentially have. 
-- This folder and alphabet_detailed folder were my first trials when it came to testing out the Warp terminal. 
-- I first started Warp with a blank slate of a project folder, and gave a simple prompt to the terminal, which was to create a game based off the only the folder name. 
-- This took 30 minutes to create and a single script connecting all the icons that Warp created. 
-- I didn't give anny adjustments to the code, which was purposeful, to test and see if the code that was provided was readable on my end or extremely long for a simple alphabet game. 
What I learned: 
-- The code and game Warp terminal provided was polished and clear when looking back at the code and the icons Warp generated. 
-- I like the potential creativity aspect of the Warp terminal, but I do think that it chose a basic alphabet designed game even though I gave it free range to do whatever. 